<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Small to median sized species (3.5-7.8 mm). Antenna extremely slender, antennomeres III-VI long (3.1-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide), VII-X shorter. Body convex. Elytra relatively narrow, 1.6-1.8 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than wide. Aedeagus asymmetric, ostium covered by a membrane; endophallic sclerites composed of two slender sclerites (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta gressitti Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F apex of tibia of middle leg, male G gonocoxae H spermatheca I abdominal ventrite V, male J abdominal ventrite V, female." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545536" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">6C, D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta houjayi sp. nov. A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E abdominal ventrite VIII F spermatheca G abdominal ventrite V, female H abdominal ventrite V, male I gonocoxae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545538" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">8C, D</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Diagnostic characters of Pyrrhalta viridipennis Kimoto A antenna, male B antenna, female C aedeagus, from Alishan (阿里山), dorsal view D ditto, lateral view E apex of aedeagus, from Shihfen (十分), dorsal view F ditto, lateral view G apex of aedeagus, from Hsiangyang, dorsal view H ditto, lateral view I abdominal ventrite VIII J gonocoxae K abdominal ventrite V, female L abdominal ventrite V, male M apex of tibia of middle leg N spermatheca." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1039.64740.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545544" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">14D</figureCitation>
